result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon J. PRESL was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

No contact with any children under the age of 18, unless approved by the agent, except his own biological children.

No contact with the victim.

Defendant must register all current and past online and/or social media accounts including user names and passwords with the agent.

Count 1 - 2nd degree sexual assault of child - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, 2nd degree sexual assault of child and count 3, obstruct officer.   Motion granted.   Court orders a pre-sentence investigation report to be completed by DOC.   Report to be filed by 03-04-16.   Sentencing hearing set for 03-11-16 at 1:30 p.m.   Defendant is ordered to submit DNA sample.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.   
Minutes.
Letter from John Laliberte, Clinical Substance Abuse Counselor.
Plea date reset to 11-10-15 at 2:00 p.m.

Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.   Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 3 for further proceedings.  Waiver of Right to Preliminary Hearing.   
ARRAIGNMENT 
Information filed.  Not guilty pleas.  Jury Calendar.   Settlement conference with the District Attorney is set for 08-25-15 at 10:00 a.m.  Plea date is set for 11-20-15 at 8:30 a.m.   State's Motion and Demand for Discovery.   
Minutes.

Defendant demands a preliminary hearing and waives the statutory time period within which a preliminary hearing must be held.   Preliminary hearing is set for 07-08-15 at 1:30 p.m.   
Minutes.
At 9:05 a.m., search warrant with return of officer thereon.
Affidavit of Detective Jennifer Pusel, Manitowoc City Police Department.
Notice of phone number change to 920-905-2991.
Search warrant issued.  RE:  Samsung Galaxy S4 Cellphone belonging to Brandon Presl.

Defendant in custody.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crimes of obstruct officer and 2nd degree sexual assault.  The matters are continued for initial appearance on 06-22-15 at 2:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $5,000.00 recognizance bond with the conditions that he have no contact with J.A.L. DOB: 01-08-01 or anyone under the age of 18 except for family members.  Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
